# GDS-VERO compliance — mandatory for UI work

When you **create or materially change React UI** (`.tsx` / `.jsx`):

1. **Follow** the **GDS-VERO compliance review** section in `GDS_FOR_LLM_AGENTS.md` (stack, imports, Chakra v3, semantic tokens, vero surfaces, typography).
2. **Complete the checklist** in that section before finishing. Fix violations in code when you can.
3. **Run lint** when available (`pnpm --filter docs lint` in monorepo; `npm run lint` / `pnpm lint` in scaffolded apps).
4. **End your reply** with the required summary sections: **Layout**, **GDS compliance**, **Accessibility**, **Lint** — including **Violation** / **Fix** pairs for any compliance issues.

Common fixes: import `Card` from `@chakra-ui/react` not `@gds-vero/react`; use `Card.Root variant="outline"` not `bg="bg.muted"`; use `GDSText textStyle="body"` not `textStyle="sm"`; page `bg="bg.subtle"`; Chakra compounds (`Dialog`, `Menu`, `Field`, …) inherit 18px body from `@gds-vero/theme` ≥ 0.1.17 — do not add manual `fontSize="sm"` unless overriding.

Canonical guide: `GDS_FOR_LLM_AGENTS.md` (monorepo root) or `node_modules/@gds-vero/react/GDS_FOR_LLM_AGENTS.md` (scaffolded apps).
